        "What happens if we now consider a scenario where we generate 100 random numbers and want to know how likely it is that more than 60 of them have a prime factor of 3? This would mean the probability that a number has a factor of 3 is $\\frac{1}{3}$ because one out of every 3 numbers will be a multiple of 3.\n",
