    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Answer 4b: REPLACE THE TEXT IN THIS CELL WITH YOUR ANSWER*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EaTdAak4U5o1"
      },
      "id": "EaTdAak4U5o1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Exploring the Gibbs Phenomenon\n",
        "\n",
        "Another interesting function is\n",
        "$$f(\\theta) = \\pi - \\theta$$ defined over the interval $0 < θ < 2\\pi$ which is extended periodically.\n",
        "which has the Fourier series\n",
        "$$2\\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{\\sin (n\\theta)}{n}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The Fourier series is an infinite sum, but in practice we always truncate it to the first $N$ terms. Thus, we really only look at *partial sums* like:\n",
        "$$2\\sum_{n=1}^N \\frac{\\sin (n\\theta)}{n}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "You can visualize and explore this truncated Fourier series compared to the function itself by running the code below and moving the slider in the resulting plot.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qBt3u8qBibmK"
      },
      "id": "qBt3u8qBibmK"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ---------- Function menu (2π-periodic on [0, 2π)) ----------\n",
        "def f_sawtooth(theta):\n",
        "    # f(x)=pi-x on [0,2π), periodic extension\n",
        "    return np.pi-theta\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------- Numerical Fourier coefficients ----------\n",
        "def fourier_coeffs_numeric(f, M=4001):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Compute a0, a_n, b_n numerically on [0, 2π] using the trapezoidal rule on a fine grid.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    x = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, M)\n",
        "    fx = f(x)\n",
        "    dx = x[1] - x[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # For a function defined on [0, 2L], L=pi here\n",
        "    a0 = (1/np.pi) * np.trapezoid(fx, x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def an(n):\n",
        "        return (1/np.pi) * np.trapezoid(fx*np.cos(n*x), x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def bn(n):\n",
        "        return (1/np.pi) * np.trapezoid(fx*np.sin(n*x), x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return a0, an, bn\n",
        "\n",
        "def partial_sum(f, N_terms=10, M=2000):\n",
        "    # Adjust x range to be from -2pi to 4pi for plotting\n",
        "    x = np.linspace(-2 * np.pi, 4 * np.pi, M)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # The function f is defined on [0, 2pi), so we need to adjust the input to f_sawtooth\n",
        "    # to ensure it's evaluated within its defined period.\n",
        "    # We use a modulo operation to make x values fall within [0, 2pi)\n",
        "    x_for_f = np.mod(x, 2 * np.pi)\n",
        "    fx = f(x_for_f)\n",
        "\n",
        "    a0, an, bn = fourier_coeffs_numeric(f_sawtooth, M=4001)\n",
        "\n",
        "    S = 0.5*a0*np.ones_like(x)\n",
        "    for n in range(1, N_terms+1):\n",
        "        S += an(n)*np.cos(n*x) + bn(n)*np.sin(n*x)\n",
        "    return x, fx, S\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------- Interactive UI ----------\n",
        "N_widget = widgets.IntSlider(\n",
        "    value=1, min=1, max=100, step=1,\n",
        "    description=\"N terms:\",\n",
        "    continuous_update=False,\n",
        "    style={\"description_width\": \"initial\"},\n",
        ")\n",
